## Phase 2–4: Domain layer

Models: User, Post, Comment, Category, Tag, plus `post_tag` pivot.

Post status: `draft`, `published`, `archived`  
Comment status: `pending`, `approved`, `rejected`

Relationships (author, category, tags, comments, replies) are set up on the Eloquent models.

---

## Phase 5–7: GraphQL API

```
graphql/
├── schema.graphql
├── types/       user, post, comment, category, tag, dashboard
├── queries/     user, post, comment, category, tag, dashboard
├── mutations/   user, post, comment, category, tag
└── inputs/      post
```

Queries cover paginated posts (title/status filters), single post by id or slug, categories, tags, comments, users, and dashboard stats.

Mutations: CRUD for posts, categories, tags, comments, users. Sensitive ones use `@guard`.

Custom validators handle unique slug/email on update for Post, Category, Tag, and User.

---

## Phase 8: REST file upload

| Method | Endpoint | Purpose |
|--------|----------|---------|
| POST | `/api/upload/post-cover` | Post cover image |
| POST | `/api/upload/avatar` | User avatar |

Returns a storage path; the path goes into GraphQL mutations when creating/updating records.

