## Phase 10: Dashboard

- Count cards for users, posts, categories, tags, comments
- Tables: recent posts/comments, top categories/tags/users
- Chart.js: posts by status, comments by status, top categories, posts over time
- `DashboardAnalytics` resolver for chart data
- Simple GraphQL query timing on the client

---

## Phase 11: Public site

Public routes are separate from admin (`/blog` vs `/posts`).

Home and blog load data through GraphQL. Guests don't see draft or archived posts on the public show page. Admin post list links to `/blog/{slug}` for preview.

---

## Phase 12: Heavy seeding

```bash
php artisan db:seed-heavy --no-interaction
```

Options in `config/heavy-seed.php` or via CLI (`--users`, `--posts`, `--comments`, `--chunk`).

Defaults: 3,000 users, 5,000 posts, 15,000 comments. Inserts run in chunks so it stays fast on a local DB.

